2500|$|Heinlein was {{surprised}} that some readers thought the book described how he believed society should be organized, explaining: [...] "I was not giving answers. I was <b>trying</b> <b>to</b> <b>shake</b> the reader loose from some preconceptions and induce him to think for himself, along new and fresh lines. In consequence, each reader gets something different out of that book because he himself supplies the answers ... It is an invitation to think – not to believe." ...|$|E
