2500|$|The {{failure of}} the Expedition only served to {{discourage}} settling in Guiana. The colony earned the nickname Enfer Vert ("Green Hell"), which it is still <b>trying</b> <b>to</b> <b>shake.</b> No other project of mass colonisation was undertaken, and the population of Whites was always drastically {{lower than that of}} the slaves. The population of the colony, of all races, did not rise above 20,000 until the gold rush (starting in 1855), [...] the second abolition of slavery in 1848 and the founding of the prisons.|$|E
